The paper discusses the use of sensors in robotics, specifically for SLAM, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also evaluates and compares the sensors based on their characteristics, which involves computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper assesses the sensors against factors critical to long-term autonomy, which involves systems and control (cs.SY).
